---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "@/components/layout/Header.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/layout/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Knicknaks"
  description="Our privacy policy: We don't collect your data. Everything runs locally in your browser."
>
  <div class="min-h-screen flex flex-col w-full">
    <Header />

    <main class="flex-1 doodle-paper py-16 md:py-24">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-6">
        <h1
          class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-8 font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--text-primary)]"
        >
          <span class="doodle-underline">Privacy Policy</span>
        </h1>

        <div
          class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none text-[var(--text-secondary)]"
        >
          <p class="lead text-xl mb-8">
            Our privacy policy is incredibly simple: <strong
              >We do not collect your data.</strong
            >
          </p>

          <h2>Client-Side Operation</h2>
          <p>
            Knicknaks is designed entirely as a suite of client-side tools. When
            you use our utilities—whether you are hashing a password, formatting
            JSON, or editing PDF metadata—the processing happens entirely on
            your own device, leveraging your web browser's innate capabilities.
          </p>
          <p>
            We do not send your text, files, or processing results to any
            backend servers. Once the initial application code is loaded, many
            of our tools can even function if you disconnect from the internet.
          </p>

          <h2>Local Storage and Persistence</h2>
          <p>
            To improve your experience, some tools may save settings or
            temporary state (such as your preferred theme or recent tool
            history) using your browser's <code>localStorage</code> or <code
              >IndexedDB</code
            > APIs. This data is stored strictly on your local hard drive and is never
            beamed back to us or any third parties. You can clear this data at any
            time by clearing your browser's site data.
          </p>

          <h2>Hosting and Analytics</h2>
          <p>
            While the application itself contains no tracking scripts or
            proprietary analytics payloads, Knicknaks is hosted on <strong
              >Cloudflare Pages</strong
            >.
          </p>
          <p>
            Cloudflare, acting as our Content Delivery Network (CDN) and hosting
            provider, processes incoming web requests to serve the initial
            application files to your browser. During this process, Cloudflare
            may collect standard server routing information (such as IP
            addresses and request headers) in order to mitigate DDoS attacks and
            ensure network reliability.
          </p>
          <p>
            You can review Cloudflare's privacy policy regarding their network
            routing infrastructure here: <a
              href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare Privacy Policy</a
            >.
          </p>

          <h2>Changes to this Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We don't have sudden plans to start hoarding data. However, if the
            underlying infrastructure changes significantly, this page will be
            updated. The core mission of Knicknaks—client-side, privacy-first
            tooling—will never change.
          </p>

          <p class="text-sm mt-12 opacity-70">Last updated: March 6, 2026</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
